                <td bgcolor="#3C4884" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/25/2004&nbsp;: 07:07:16 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> Shammies need all the help they can get. They are a massively boring class to play. In a normal LDoN their malos+slow cycle finishes when the mob is around 60/70% hp. Not arguing that they don't help the group a lot with malos especially if it's caster heavy, just saying they are really, really boring to play. Malo, slow, buff == most raid duties. Malo, slow, buff, cast FA is about all they do in LDoN, with an occasional heal thrown on.<br /><br />Like it was mentioned they really have -very- limited options when it comes to actually using their mana. They have a lot of long duration dots (useless in ldon) a few short duration dots with no way to ditch aggro; saryns+curse+slow == a ton of aggro on them with no way to get rid of it.<br /><br />The problem is a kunark era one. When you give a class a 75% massively overpowering slow in low 50s, where do they go from there?<br /><br />If you are in love with mindless mana regen, start a shammy. Sit around FM all day with a lot of clicking, malo a mob, slow it, throw in a heal..yes, much more appealing than what a necro can do.<br /><br />In easy LDoN's BL are my preferred slower on my sk and nec. Fast casting, its a 65 spell and not really that resisted(even in hard LDoN, there's a good chance someone in group can debuff if necessary. Plus very nice DPS / sd / paragon.<br /><br />If I was a shammy I would bitch nonstop :-)</span></font></td>
